beginner.name: walk on treadmill
beginner.description: A treadmill is a fitness machine that allows you to walk, jog, or run indoors while simulating the motion of walking or running outdoors. The machine typically has a conveyor belt that moves at varying speeds and inclines, allowing users to control the intensity and duration of their workouts.

beginner.name: elliptical
beginner.description: An elliptical machine, also known as a cross trainer, is a piece of fitness equipment that simulates the motion of running, walking, or stair climbing while putting less stress on the joints. It typically consists of two pedals that move in an elliptical pattern, and can be adjusted to simulate different levels of resistance and intensity.

beginner.name: stationary_bike
beginner.description: A stationary bike, also known as an exercise bike, is a piece of fitness equipment that simulates the motion of riding a bicycle while staying in place. It typically consists of a seat, pedals, and handlebars, and can be adjusted to simulate different levels of resistance and intensity. Stationary bikes are popular in gyms and fitness centers, and can also be used at home for cardiovascular exercise and lower body conditioning.

intermediate.name: burpees

intermediate.name: stair_climber
intermediate.description: A stair climber, also known as a stair stepper or step machine, is a fitness machine that simulates climbing stairs. It typically consists of a set of pedals or steps that move up and down, creating a repetitive motion similar to climbing stairs. Stair climbers provide a low-impact cardiovascular workout that targets the muscles in the lower body, including the quadriceps, hamstrings, calves, and glutes.
